OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJapan arrests alleged      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fringleaders of crime spree 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Japanese police have arrested four men 
OL,6, for allegedly orchestrating scams and  
OL,7, robberies while jailed overseas, in a  
OL,8, case that has gripped the country.     
OL,10,FAuthorities say they targeted the      
OL,11,Felderly, and stole or cheated their    
OL,12,Fvictims of billions of yen.            
OL,14,FFrom their jail in the Philippines, the
OL,15,Fmen managed to recruit accomplices in  
OL,16,FJapan to carry out the robberies.      
OL,18,FOne of them is said to be the          
OL,19,Fmastermind, who calls himself "Luffy"  
OL,20,Fafter a popular anime character.       
